title: 'Supernatural' Season 11 Episode 2 Spoilers: Dean Leaves Sam for Jenna
text:
'Supernatural' Season 11 Episode 2 Spoilers: Dean Leaves Sam for Jenna 0 By Jess Dailo , Christian Post Contributor October 10, 2015 | 2:29 pm The CW Jared Padalecki and Jensen Ackles in "Supernatural" 
The second episode of "Supernatural" season 11 is expected to show some action-packed scenes with the siblings. 
The upcoming episode is titled "Form and Void," which will feature Sam, played by Jared Padalecki, and Dean, played by Jensen Ackles, trying to tackle the aftermath of the previous season. 
While the premiere did not exactly satisfy the fans' cravings for a monster takedown, it was reported that the siblings will finally see some action. 
The previous episode saw Jenna in danger, which had urged her to call upon Dean in order to save her. It was reported that Dean will have the dilemma of choosing to save Jenna over taking care of the town. 
The situation had Sam beginning to challenge their purpose. He said, "When did we forget how to do this? Dean, if we don't change, right now, all of our crap is just going to keep repeating ourselvesâ€¦ Saving people means all of the people, not just that baby, not just each other." 
However, it was reported that it will be Sam himself who will push Dean into the decision of helping Jenna out. The episode will see Sam and Dean stuck in a town with citizens infected by a gas that will cause a monstrous disaster. 
As reported by Spoilers Guide , it was reported that the two will be in a predicament when Sammy is left alone after Dean leaves to take Jenna, played by Laci J. Mailey, home. Jenna was a nurse that Dean had met after Darkness was unleashed. 
Unfortunately, the episode will see Sam struggling with his solo battle. It will be evident that he is not equipped or prepared for the upcoming obstacles that the city will bring. 
"Supernatural" season 11 episode 2 titled "Form and Void" is expected to air on CW this Oct. 14.
